Description: inhibitor of the host RecBCD nuclease in the λ Red system; gam; protects the double-stranded DNA substrate for recombination

VBET_LAMBD - Also known as betA, red-beta, redB. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Gene bet protein functions in general recombination and in the late, rolling-circle mode of lambda DNA replication. Has a function similar to that of E.coli recT. It is a single-stranded DNA binding protein that can promote renaturation of DNA. From Escherichia phage lambda (Bacteriophage lambda).

EXO_LAMBD - Also known as red-alpha, redX. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Facilitates phage DNA recombination through the double-strand break repair (DSBR) and single-strand annealing pathways. Also important for the late, rolling-circle mode of lambda DNA replication. From Escherichia phage lambda (Bacteriophage lambda).
